1 eye, those rules shall provide for a sample hand-to-eye count of the paper
2 ballots of a sampling of a statewide ballot item in every county. The
3 presidential ballot item shall be the subject of the sampling in a presidential
4 election. If there is no statewide ballot item, the State Board shall provide a
5 process for selecting district or local ballot items to adequately sample the
6 electorate. The State Board shall approve in an open meeting the procedure
7 for random sampling for each election. The random sampling for any county
8 shall be done publicly after the initial count of election returns for that county
9 is publicly released or 24 hours after the polls close on election day, whichever
10 is earlier. The sample chosen by the State Board shall be of one or more full
11 precincts, full counts of mailed absentee ballots, and full counts of one or more
12 early voting sites. The size of the sample of each category shall be chosen to
13 produce a statistically significant result and shall be chosen after consultation
14 with a statistician. The actual units shall be chosen at random. In the event of
15 a material discrepancy between the electronic or mechanical count and a
16 hand-to-eye count, the hand-to-eye count shall control, except where paper
17 ballots have been lost or destroyed or where there is another reasonable basis
18 to conclude that the hand-to-eye count is not the true count. If the discrepancy
19 between the hand-to-eye count and the mechanical or electronic count is
20 significant, a complete hand-to-eye count shall be conducted. The sample
21 count need not be done on election night.
22 (3) The rules shall provide for accurate unofficial reporting of the results from the
23 precinct to the county board of elections with reasonable speed on the night
24 of the election.
25 (4) The rules shall provide for the prompt and secure transmission of official
26 ballots from the voting place to the county board of elections.board.
27 (c) The State Board shall direct the county boards of elections in the application of the
28 principles and rules in individual circumstances."
