28 "§ 163-41. Precinct chief judges and judges of election; appointment; terms of office;
29 qualifications; vacancies; oaths of office.
30 (a) Appointment of Chief Judge and Judges. – At the meeting required by G.S. 163-31 to
31 be held on the Tuesday following the third Monday in August of the year in which they are
32 appointed, the county board of elections shall appoint one person to act as chief judge and two
33 other persons to act as judges of election for each precinct in the county. Their terms of office
34 shall continue for two years from the specified date of appointment and until their successors are
35 appointed and qualified, except that if a nonresident of the precinct is appointed as chief judge
36 or judge for a precinct, that person's term of office shall end if the county board of elections
37 appoints a qualified resident of the precinct of the same party to replace the nonresident chief
38 judge or judge. It shall be their the duty of the precinct officials to conduct the primaries and
39 elections within their respective precincts. Persons appointed to these offices must be registered
40 voters and residents of the county in which the precinct is located, of good repute, and able to
41 read and write. Not more than one judge in each precinct shall belong to the same political party
42 as the chief judge.
