31 BAN RANK CHOICE VOTING
32 SECTION 2.5.(a) Article 14A of Chapter 163 of the General Statutes is amended by
33 adding a new section to read:
34 "§ 163-165.6A. Rank choice voting prohibited.
35 No rank choice voting may be used in any referendum, primary, or other election. The term
36 "rank choice voting" refers to a method that allows a voter the option to rank candidates for office
37 in the voter's order of preference."
38 SECTION 2.5.(b) This section becomes effective January 1, 2026, and applies to
39 elections held on or after that date.
40
