32 (6) Serve as a member of any other State board, as defined in G.S. 138A-3.
33 (7) Make written or oral statements intended for general distribution or
34 dissemination to the public at large encouraging or promoting voter turnout in
35 any election."
36 SECTION 3.1.(b) G.S. 163-30 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
37 "(g) No person while serving on a county board shall do any of the following:
38 (1) Make written or oral statements intended for general distribution or
39 dissemination to the public at large supporting or opposing the nomination or
40 election of one or more clearly identified candidates for public office,
41 supporting any political party over another, or influencing voter turnout for a
42 particular political party.
43 (2) Make written or oral statements intended for general distribution or
44 dissemination to the public at large supporting or opposing the passage of one
45 or more clearly identified referendum or ballot issue proposals.
46 (3) Make written or oral statements intended for general distribution or
47 dissemination to the public at large encouraging or promoting voter turnout in
48 any election."
49 SECTION 3.1.(c) This section becomes effective January 1, 2026, and applies to
50 elections held on or after that date.
