25 PART IV. REVISIONS TO UNIFORM MILITARY AND OVERSEAS VOTERS ACT
26
27 PHOTO ID REQUIRED FOR UOCAVA VOTERS
28 SECTION 4.1.(a) G.S. 163-258.10 reads as rewritten:
29 "§ 163-258.10. Timely casting Casting of ballot.
30 (a) To be valid, a military-overseas ballot shall either be received by the appropriate
31 county board of elections no later than the close of the polls, or the covered voter shall submit
32 the ballot for mailing, electronic transmission, or other authorized means of delivery not later
33 than 12:01 A.M., at the place where the voter completes the ballot, on the date of the election.
34 (b) The covered voter shall submit the military-overseas ballot with a form of
35 identification that contains a photograph of the covered voter as described in G.S. 163-166.16(a)
36 or an affidavit as described in G.S. 163-166.16(d)(1), (d)(2), or (d)(3). The State Board shall
37 provide the means for any identification electronically submitted in accordance with this
38 subsection to be submitted in a secure manner."
39 SECTION 4.1.(b) This section becomes effective January 1, 2026, and applies to
40 elections held on or after that date.
