1 d. Any business entity that is organized under the law of, or has its
2 principal place of business in, a foreign country.
3 e. Any business entity organized and operating in the United States that
4 is wholly or majority owned by a foreign national or combination of
5 foreign nationals."
6 SECTION 5.2.(b) Article 22A of Chapter 163 of the General Statutes is amended
7 by adding a new section to read:
8 "§ 163-278.19C. Contributions by foreign nationals.
9 (a) A referendum committee shall not accept any contributions from a foreign national,
10 except as provided in this section.
11 (b) A referendum committee may accept a contribution from a foreign national as defined
12 in G.S. 163-278.6(52)e. if all of the following are met:
13 (1) The contribution is derived solely from funds generated by operations in the
14 United States.
15 (2) All decisions concerning the contribution are made by an individual or group
16 of individuals who are citizens or lawful permanent residents of the United
17 States."
18 SECTION 5.2.(c) This section becomes effective January 1, 2026, and applies to
19 contributions made or accepted on or after that date.
